about.summary: Fit linear and generalized linear mixed models with various extensions, including zero-inflation. The models are fitted using maximum likelihood estimation via 'TMB' (Template Model Builder). Random effects are assumed to be Gaussian on the scale of the linear predictor and are integrated out using the Laplace approximation. Gradients are calculated using automatic differentiation.

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.1.8" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-glmmtmb
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/glmmTMB_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/glmmTMB/glmmTMB_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 4248f6c37a2f82543bc0160c71d6d409ff742a4b1b29b417a42f34460489bd14

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcppeigen
    - r-tmb >=1.9.0
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_18.9000
    - r-mgcv
    - r-nlme
    - r-numderiv
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-matrix
    - r-rcppeigen
    - r-tmb >=1.9.0
    - r-lme4 >=1.1_18.9000
    - r-mgcv
    - r-nlme
    - r-numderiv

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('glmmTMB')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('glmmTMB')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/glmmTMB
  license: AGPL-3.0-only
  summary: Fit linear and generalized linear mixed models with various extensions, including zero-inflation. The models are fitted using maximum likelihood estimation via 'TMB' (Template Model Builder). Random effects are assumed to be Gaussian on the scale of the linear predictor and are integrated out using the Laplace
    approximation. Gradients are calculated using automatic differentiation.
  license_family: AGPL
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/AGPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - ccwang002
